HEADWORD: Merovingian
<hw>Mer`o*vin"gi*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[From
<persfn><etsep>Merovaeus</etsep></persfn>, the Latin name of a king of
the Franks.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to the first Frankish dynasty
in Gaul or France.</def> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>One of the kings of
this dynasty.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

